From: evdi-5120x1440-fix
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] connector: inject synthetic 5120x1440@60 mode when EDID omits it

Some docks (e.g. ThinkPad Hybrid USB-C Dock, USB ID 17e9:6015) pass a
truncated EDID to EVDI: the Samsung Odyssey G93SC (32:9, 5120x1440)
reports EDID Extension Block Count: 3, but DisplayLinkManager forwards
only 2 blocks (256 bytes). The extension blocks containing the 5120x1440
detailed timing descriptors are silently dropped.

As a result, drm_add_edid_modes() never sees the native resolution and
the compositor has no 5120x1440 mode to offer, despite the hardware
supporting it on Windows with the same dock.

Inject a synthetic CVT reduced-blanking 5120x1440@60 mode after
drm_add_edid_modes() when the mode is absent from the EDID-derived list.
The mode then goes through evdi_mode_valid() and is accepted provided
pixel throughput is within the device limit.

Note: the root fix belongs in DisplayLinkManager (closed source), which
should forward the full EDID. This patch is a kernel-side workaround
until that is addressed upstream by Synaptics/DisplayLink.

Tested-on: Samsung Odyssey G93SC (32:9, 5120x1440) via ThinkPad Hybrid
           USB-C with USB-A Dock (17e9:6015), Linux 6.17, EVDI 1.14.16

Signed-off-by: evdi-5120x1440-fix
---
 evdi_connector.c | 21 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+)

--- a/evdi_connector.c
+++ b/evdi_connector.c
@@ -58,6 +58,27 @@ static int evdi_get_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)

 	ret = drm_add_edid_modes(connector, edid);
 	EVDI_INFO("(card%d) Edid property set\n", evdi->dev_index);
+
+	/* Inject 5120x1440@60 if EDID truncated by dock firmware */
+	{
+		struct drm_display_mode *m, *mode_5120 = NULL;
+		bool found = false;
+
+		list_for_each_entry(m, &connector->probed_modes, head) {
+			if (m->hdisplay == 5120 && m->vdisplay == 1440) {
+				found = true;
+				break;
+			}
+		}
+		if (!found) {
+			mode_5120 = drm_cvt_mode(connector->dev, 5120, 1440, 60, true, false, false);
+			if (mode_5120) {
+				drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode_5120);
+				ret++;
+				EVDI_INFO("(card%d) Injected synthetic 5120x1440@60\n", evdi->dev_index);
+			}
+		}
+	}
 err:
 	kfree(edid);
 	return ret;
